cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper discusses a methodology for adapting POS taggers to new domains without the need for a manually annotated corpus. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL. The paper also mentions the use of suffix information and orthographic information, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and data mining, falling under cs.LG and cs.IR. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of unsupervised learning, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
